<h3>Re: HP Pavilion laptop drivers.</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>ALL drivers that are for the CPU are going to have to be updated in Windows. Unless of course if HP allows Linux Upgrades. ( Not Happening )&#160; So in response to your Touch -Pad,&#160; you may install this either in Synaptic or use this command: sudo apt-get install xserver-xorg-input-touchpad</p>
</div>
<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr/><p>-Jeff Szydel </p><p>*Parrot Ambassador&#160; &#160;*Social Groups Manager&#160; &#160;*Helpdesk&#160; &#160;*Wiki Editor&#160; &#160; <br/>*Parrot Telegram Group Administrator&#160; &#160;*Parrot Community Administrator</p></div>
