<h3>Re: HP Pavilion laptop drivers.</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<div class="quotebox"><cite>root wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>The WiFi itself works fine.. I don&#039;t know how that came up. I was more just worried about any other drivers. You know, graphics, firmware. Anything that may be missing.</p></div></blockquote></div><p>The kernel has builtin drivers: brcmfmac<br/>For the rest of the drivers, depend which HP model do you have, ATI, Nvidia, Intel.&#160; for most of them the drivers are working fine. Mine has an ATI Radeon and works without trouble. <br/>Regarding the BIOS updates, do you really need to update it?. I mean, have you read the changelog and see what exactly are the fixes, and decided if you need them?</p><br/><div class="quotebox"><cite>Jeff wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><p>Broadcom Drivers are also an issue because the Broadcom is not compatible to Monitor Mode.&#160; I do have a fix for you to get internet with the Broadcom driver just for browsing. but the tools and the Wifi cracking will not work.&#160; Let me know if you can plug in ethernet and install the dkms and if need be i will give you the commands</p></div></blockquote></div><p>I havent tested in Parrot, but in Arch the broadcom-wl driver does support monitor mode. <br/>Just do:</p><p>echo 1 &gt; /proc/brcm_monitor0</p>
</div>
